<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/d148d6c83f05b49cd7122247df2a885e.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 7 and A = 15 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>26.1</li><li>27.0</li><li>75.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({15}\right)}}}=\frac{{7}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{7}}{{\tan{{\left({15}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{26.124355652982}\approx{26.1}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={7}^{{2}}+{26.124355652982}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={49}+{682.4819582835}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={731.4819582835}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{731.4819582835}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{27.045923136094}\approx{27}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{15}^{\circ}\approx{75}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

